en_3438795_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – Fishermen have been advised to refrain from fairing out to sea until 6 am tomorrow (October 03).
en_3438795_1	The Department of Fisheries states the directive is issued as the sea extending from Hambanthota to Pottuvil and Puttalam to Negombo are expected to be rough with the occurrence of thundershowers.
en_3438795_2	08.15 am – An advisory for heavy rains and strong winds has been issued by the Natural Hazards Early Warning Centre of the Meteorology Department.
en_3438795_3	There is a high possibility of severe thunderstorms and rough seas due to strong winds over 70-80 kmph.
en_3438795_4	Rough seas are expected off the coast extending from Matara to Pottuvil as well as the coast extending from Puttalam to Negombo.
en_3438795_5	Fishing communities have been asked to take extra caution.
